**COTAK.GOV FAQs**

**1\. How do I reset a forgotten password?**

* Direct user to [cotak.gov](http://cotak.gov)   
* In upper right corner of website select LOG IN → Type in agency email address → Forgot your password → Email password reset link  
    
  ![][image1]  
    
* Navigate to the password reset link in your email.

![][image2]![][image3]

* Reconnect to the COTAK server in your TAK app once your password has been reset.

**2\. Why can’t I connect to the COTAK Server?**

* Make sure the user’s password is correct by having them use their agency email and password to sign into [cotak.gov](http://cotak.gov). Follow password reset steps above if password is incorrect  
* If password is correct, try one or more of the following 6 options:   
1. Delete and re-add server

    ![][image4]

2. If user has a personal VPN on their phone, ask them to disable it  
3. Disconnect from an agency wifi (this often blocks COTAK server connection)  
4. Force reset user’s password: In the admin tools of cotak.gov navigate to the bottom of the user’s page to assign a temporary password

   ![][image5]

5. Delete and re-install the ATAK or iTAK app

**3\. Why isn’t my GPS working?**

* Make sure your location services are set to “Always Allow” in your device settings   
* Go outside to get your location to show up for the first time

**4\. How can I add or remove an agency administrator?**  
The current agency administrator can send a by name request for the action to the COTAK System Administrator(s) through submitting a support ticket or emailing [support@cotak.gov](mailto:support@cotak.gov). Once the new Agency Administrator is vetted and approved, the System Administrators will review the user profile and ensure the appropriate levels of access are given. 

**5\. What can be integrated into COTAK?**  
We can integrate any device as long as it has a data feed going out and the CAD vendor has an API. Below are some examples of integrations:

* Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) systems  
* UAS   
* Inreach/SPOT devices  
* Covert Trackers

See our About page for a [full list of integrations](https://cotak.gov/pages/system-integrations/existing-integrations). Submit a support ticket or email [support@cotak.gov](mailto:support@cotak.gov) for any integration requests.

**6\. I am a private Colorado-based first responder. Can I use COTAK?**  
We are happy to get you set up with COTAK, but you will need to have a sponsor from a State of Colorado Agency. All that we will need from you is a letter signed by a member of a state agency (Fire Department, Sheriff's Office etc.) which states that they would like your organization to be onboarded to COTAK.

**7\. I am a first responder not based out of Colorado. What options do I have?**  
Unfortunately, COTAK is only available for Colorado first responders at this time. We hope in the future to be able to license the software for free to other states for their use, however that is still quite a ways out. There are several resources that are available to groups that would like to use TAK. The FreeTakServer group is sponsored by the Air Force Research Lab and may be a useful resource for a larger than hobby-scale deployment.

**8\. Can I be part of multiple agencies?**  
Yes, you can be part of multiple agencies. You will still use the same login information, you will just have access to additional channels.
